The paper focuses on Active Learning (AL) for Deep Bayesian Active Learning, which is a subfield of Machine Learning (ML). Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with image datasets, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of Hilbert Schmidt Independence Criterion (HSIC) for measuring the dependency between a candidate batch of points and the unlabeled set suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses optimizations for scaling the method to large unlabeled sets, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
